article.headline: Dartmouth 73, Harvard 56
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Alex Barnett scored 21 points, DeVon Mosley added 17 and John Ball grabbed 10 rebounds as Dartmouth snapped a four-game losing streak with a 73-56 win over Harvard on Friday night. Dartmouth (6-8, 1-1 Ivy League) held Harvard (6-12, 1-1) to two field goals over the final 11:30 and to a season-low 34.6 percent shooting from the field. Jeremy Linn and Evan Harris each scored 16 for Harvard, which had won its last two games. Dartmouth jumped out to a 9-2 lead and never trailed. The Big Green shot 57.1 percent in the first half to take a 36-26 lead. Harvard got as close as six points twice in the second half. Trailing 59-52 with 5:33 remaining, the Crimson missed its final six field goal attempts and was just 4-of-10 from the foul line the rest of the way. Dartmouth went 5-for-10 from the 3-point arc and 12-for-15 from foul line on the game.
